title: How to ensure program runs on windows ce6.0 device environment?
body: I have a program at work that deploys pages to a web server via C# code in a .NET framework and I have already deployed one of the sites successfully with the layout I want, but for the second which acts nearly identical to the first and has all the same code (only has a different file path for reading the page data) I cannot seem to get it to run on the CE environment. I check the MS VS Process Viewer after adding the file and it won't seem to run it at all no matter what I do. My question is, is this merely an error somewhere in the program halting it's execution that I need to look for and debug or could there be another reason why I cannot get it on there?
